Argentine Workers Lift Blockades at YPF Oil Fields, Clarin Says

-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 
2011-05-17T11:53:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/argentine-workers-lift-blockades-at-ypf-oil-fields-clarin-says.html
Argentine construction workers last
night lifted blockades at  YPF SA (YPFD)  oil and gas fields in the
southern Argentine province of Chubut after pay talks started,
newspaper Clarin  reported , without saying how it obtained the
information.  The construction workers, who work in the YPF fields, are
claiming a 25,000 peso ($6,120.25) bonus payment that has been
granted to workers from other unions, the Buenos Aires-based
paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in  Buenos Aires  at 
 rorihuela@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  